s, and so on. Beyond doubt their book is the most wise and original contribution to accounting theory since Professor Bonbright wrote 'The Valuation of Property' a quarter of a century ago.";--The Economist  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aIncome. 0aProfit. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh1 aBell, Philip W., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520340626?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520340626423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520340626/original  aEBA_EMB  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles